{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["27-DAN-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "DAN"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["Daniel \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["The Book of Daniel \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["Daniel \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["Dan \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt2", "content": ["The Book of \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["Daniel \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "DAN 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DAN 1:1"}, "In the third year of the reign of Jehoiakim king of Judah Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came to Jerusalem and besieged\nit. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DAN 1:2"}, "The Lord", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:2 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word translated \u201cLord\u201d is \u201cAdonai.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " gave Jehoiakim king of Judah into his hand, with part\nof the vessels of the house of Allah; ", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:2 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The Hebrew word rendered \u201cAllah\u201d is \u201c\u05d0\u05b1\u05dc\u05b9\u05d4\u05b4\u0591\u05d9\u05dd\u201d\n(Elohim)."]}], "caller": "+"}, " and he carried them into the land of Shinar to the house of his god. He brought the vessels into the treasure\nhouse of his god. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DAN 1:3"}, "The king spoke to Ashpenaz the master of his eunuchs, that he should bring in some of the children of Israel, even of the\nroyal offspring", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:3 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, seed"]}], "caller": "+"}, " and of the nobles; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DAN 1:4"}, "youths in whom was no defect, but well-favoured, and skilful in all wisdom, and endowed with knowledge, and understanding\nscience, and who had the ability to stand in the king\u2019s palace; and that he should teach them the learning and the language of\nthe Chaldeans. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DAN 1:5"}, "The king appointed for them a daily portion of the king\u2019s dainties, and of the wine which he drank, and that they should\nbe nourished three years; that at its end they should stand before the king.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DAN 1:6"}, "Now amongst these were of the children of Judah: Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DAN 1:7"}, "The prince of the eunuchs gave names to them: to Daniel he gave the name Belteshazzar; to Hananiah, Shadrach; to Mishael,\nMeshach; and to Azariah, Abednego. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DAN 1:8"}, "But Daniel purposed in his heart that he would not defile himself with the king\u2019s dainties, nor with the wine which he\ndrank. Therefore he requested of the prince of the eunuchs that he might not defile himself.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DAN 1:9"}, "Now Allah made Daniel find kindness and compassion in the sight of the prince of the eunuchs.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DAN 1:10"}, "The prince of the eunuchs said to Daniel, \u201cI fear my lord the king, who has appointed your food and your drink. For why\nshould he see your faces worse looking than the youths who are of your own age? Then you would endanger my head with the king.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DAN 1:11"}, "Then Daniel said to the steward whom the prince of the eunuchs had appointed over Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DAN 1:12"}, "\u201cTest your servants, I beg you, ten days; and let them give us vegetables to eat, and water to drink.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DAN 1:13"}, "Then let our faces be examined before you, and the face of the youths who eat of the king\u2019s dainties; and as you see,\ndeal with your servants.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DAN 1:14"}, "So he listened to them in this matter, and tested them for ten days.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DAN 1:15"}, "At the end of ten days, their faces appeared fairer, and they were fatter in flesh, than all the youths who ate of the\nking\u2019s dainties. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DAN 1:16"}, "So the steward took away their dainties, and the wine that they would drink, and gave them vegetables.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DAN 1:17"}, "Now as for these four youths, Allah gave them knowledge and skill in all learning and wisdom; and Daniel had\nunderstanding in all visions and dreams. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DAN 1:18"}, "At the end of the days which the king had appointed for bringing them in, the prince of the eunuchs brought them in\nbefore Nebuchadnezzar. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DAN 1:19"}, "The king talked with them; and amongst them all was found no one like Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah. Therefore\nstood they before the king. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DAN 1:20"}, "In every matter of wisdom and understanding, concerning which the king enquired of them, he found them ten times better\nthan all the magicians and enchanters who were in all his realm.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DAN 1:21"}, "Daniel continued even to the first year of king Dhul-Qarnayn.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "DAN 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DAN 2:1"}, "In the second year of the reign of Nebuchadnezzar, Nebuchadnezzar dreamt dreams; and his spirit was troubled, and his\nsleep went from him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DAN 2:2"}, "Then the king commanded that the magicians, the enchanters, the sorcerers, and the Chaldeans be called to tell the king\nhis dreams. So they came in and stood before the king. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DAN 2:3"}, "The king said to them, \u201cI have dreamt a dream, and my spirit is troubled to know the dream.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DAN 2:4"}, "Then the Chaldeans spoke to the king in the Syrian language, \u201cO king, live forever! Tell your servants the dream, and we\nwill show the interpretation.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DAN 2:5"}, "The king answered the Chaldeans, \u201cThe thing has gone from me. If you don\u2019t make known to me the dream and its\ninterpretation, you will be cut in pieces, and your houses will be made a dunghill.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DAN 2:6"}, "But if you show the dream and its interpretation, you will receive of me gifts and rewards and great honour. Therefore\nshow me the dream and its interpretation.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DAN 2:7"}, "They answered the second time and said, \u201cLet the king tell his servants the dream, and we will show the interpretation.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DAN 2:8"}, "The king answered, \u201cI know of a certainty that you are trying to gain time, because you see the thing has gone from me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DAN 2:9"}, "But if you don\u2019t make known to me the dream, there is but one law for you; for you have prepared lying and corrupt words\nto speak before me, until the situation changes. Therefore tell me the dream, and I will know that you can show me its\ninterpretation.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DAN 2:10"}, "The Chaldeans answered before the king, and said, \u201cThere is not a man on the earth who can show the king\u2019s matter,\nbecause no king, lord, or ruler, has asked such a thing of any magician, or enchanter, or Chaldean.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DAN 2:11"}, "It is a rare thing that the king requires, and there is no other who can show it before the king, except the gods, whose\ndwelling is not with flesh.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DAN 2:12"}, "Because of this, the king was angry and very furious, and commanded that all the wise men of Babylon be destroyed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DAN 2:13"}, "So the decree went out, and the wise men were to be slain. They sought Daniel and his companions to be slain.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DAN 2:14"}, "Then Daniel returned answer with counsel and prudence to Arioch the captain of the king\u2019s guard, who had gone out to kill\nthe wise men of Babylon. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DAN 2:15"}, "He answered Arioch the king\u2019s captain, \u201cWhy is the decree so urgent from the king?\u201d Then Arioch made the thing known to\nDaniel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DAN 2:16"}, "Daniel went in, and desired of the king that he would appoint him a time, and he would show the king the interpretation.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DAN 2:17"}, "Then Daniel went to his house and made the thing known to Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah, his companions:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DAN 2:18"}, "that they would desire mercies of Allah of heaven concerning this secret; that Daniel and his companions would not perish\nwith the rest of the wise men of Babylon. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DAN 2:19"}, "Then the secret was revealed to Daniel in a vision of the night. Then Daniel blessed Allah of heaven.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DAN 2:20"}, "Daniel answered, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cBlessed be the name of Allah forever and ever; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for wisdom and might are his. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DAN 2:21"}, "He changes the times and the seasons. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He removes kings, and sets up kings. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He gives wisdom to the wise, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and knowledge to those who have understanding. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DAN 2:22"}, "He reveals the deep and secret things. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He knows what is in the darkness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the light dwells with him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DAN 2:23"}, "I thank you, and praise you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["you Allah of my fathers, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["who have given me wisdom and might, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and have now made known to me what we desired of you; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for you have made known to us the king\u2019s matter.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DAN 2:24"}, "Therefore Daniel went in to Arioch, whom the king had appointed to destroy the wise men of Babylon. He went and said this\nto him: \u201cDon\u2019t destroy the wise men of Babylon. Bring me in before the king, and I will show to the king the interpretation.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DAN 2:25"}, "Then Arioch brought in Daniel before the king in haste, and said this to him: \u201cI have found a man of the children of the\ncaptivity of Judah who will make known to the king the interpretation.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DAN 2:26"}, "The king answered Daniel, whose name was Belteshazzar, \u201cAre you able to make known to me the dream which I have seen, and\nits interpretation?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DAN 2:27"}, "Daniel answered before the king, and said, \u201cThe secret which the king has demanded can\u2019t be shown to the king by wise\nmen, enchanters, magicians, or soothsayers; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DAN 2:28"}, "but there is Allah in heaven who reveals secrets, and he has made known to the king Nebuchadnezzar what will be in the\nlatter days. Your dream, and the visions of your head on your bed, are these:\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "DAN 2:29"}, "\u201cAs for you, O king, your thoughts came on your bed, what should happen hereafter; and he who reveals secrets has made\nknown to you what will happen. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "DAN 2:30"}, "But as for me, this secret is not revealed to me for any wisdom that I have more than any living, but to the intent that\nthe interpretation may be made known to the king, and that you may know the thoughts of your heart.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "DAN 2:31"}, "\u201cYou, O king, saw, and behold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:31 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBehold\u201d, from \u201c\u05d4\u05b4\u05e0\u05bc\u05b5\u05d4\u201d, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or\ngaze at. It is often used as an interjection."]}], "caller": "+"}, " a great image. This image, which was mighty, and whose brightness was\nexcellent, stood before you; and its appearance was terrifying. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "DAN 2:32"}, "As for this image, its head was of fine gold, its breast and its arms of silver, its belly and its thighs of bronze,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "DAN 2:33"}, "its legs of iron, its feet part of iron, and part of clay.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "DAN 2:34"}, "You saw until a stone was cut out without hands, which struck the image on its feet that were of iron and clay, and broke\nthem in pieces. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "DAN 2:35"}, "Then the iron, the clay, the bronze, the silver, and the gold were broken in pieces together, and became like the chaff\nof the summer threshing floors. The wind carried them away, so that no place was found for them. The stone that struck the\nimage became a great mountain, and filled the whole earth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "DAN 2:36"}, "\u201cThis is the dream; and we will tell its interpretation before the king.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "DAN 2:37"}, "You, O king, are king of kings, to whom Allah of heaven has given the kingdom, the power, the strength, and the glory.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "DAN 2:38"}, "Wherever the children of men dwell, he has given the animals of the field and the birds of the sky into your hand, and\nhas made you rule over them all. You are the head of gold. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "DAN 2:39"}, "\u201cAfter you, another kingdom will arise that is inferior to you; and another third kingdom of bronze, which will rule over\nall the earth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "DAN 2:40"}, "The fourth kingdom will be strong as iron, because iron breaks in pieces and subdues all things; and as iron that crushes\nall these, it will break in pieces and crush. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "DAN 2:41"}, "Whereas you saw the feet and toes, part of potters\u2019 clay, and part of iron, it will be a divided kingdom; but there will\nbe in it of the strength of the iron, because you saw the iron mixed with miry clay.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "DAN 2:42"}, "As the toes of the feet were part of iron, and part of clay, so the kingdom will be partly strong, and partly broken.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "DAN 2:43"}, "Whereas you saw the iron mixed with miry clay, they will mingle themselves with the seed of men; but they won\u2019t cling to\none another, even as iron does not mix with clay. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "DAN 2:44"}, "\u201cIn the days of those kings Allah of heaven will set up a kingdom which will never be destroyed, nor will its sovereignty\nbe left to another people; but it will break in pieces and consume all these kingdoms, and it will stand forever.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "DAN 2:45"}, "Because you saw that a stone was cut out of the mountain without hands, and that it broke in pieces the iron, the bronze,\nthe clay, the silver, and the gold; the great Allah has made known to the king what will happen hereafter. The dream is\ncertain, and its interpretation sure.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "DAN 2:46"}, "Then the king Nebuchadnezzar fell on his face, worshipped Daniel, and commanded that they should offer an offering and\nsweet odours to him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "DAN 2:47"}, "The king answered to Daniel, and said, \u201cOf a truth your Allah is Allah of gods, and the Lord of kings, and a revealler of\nsecrets, since you have been able to reveal this secret.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "DAN 2:48"}, "Then the king made Daniel great, and gave him many great gifts, and made him rule over the whole province of Babylon, and\nto be chief governor over all the wise men of Babylon. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "DAN 2:49"}, "Daniel requested of the king, and he appointed Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego over the affairs of the province of\nBabylon; but Daniel was in the king\u2019s gate. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "DAN 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DAN 3:1"}, "Nebuchadnezzar the king made an image of gold, whose height was sixty\ncubits,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man\u2019s arm, or about 18\ninches or 46 centimetres."]}], "caller": "+"}, " and its width six cubits. He set it up in the plain of Dura, in the province of Babylon.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DAN 3:2"}, "Then Nebuchadnezzar the king sent to gather together the local governors, the deputies, and the governors, the judges, the\ntreasurers, the counsellors, the sheriffs, and all the rulers of the provinces, to come to the dedication of the image which\nNebuchadnezzar the king had set up. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DAN 3:3"}, "Then the local governors, the deputies, and the governors, the judges, the treasurers, the counsellors, the sheriffs, and\nall the rulers of the provinces, were gathered together to the dedication of the image that Nebuchadnezzar the king had set up;\nand they stood before the image that Nebuchadnezzar had set up. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DAN 3:4"}, "Then the herald cried aloud, \u201cTo you it is commanded, peoples, nations, and languages,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DAN 3:5"}, "that whenever you hear the sound of the horn, flute, zither, lyre, harp, pipe, and all kinds of music, you fall down and\nworship the golden image that Nebuchadnezzar the king has set up.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DAN 3:6"}, "Whoever doesn\u2019t fall down and worship shall be cast into the middle of a burning fiery furnace the same hour.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DAN 3:7"}, "Therefore at that time, when all the peoples heard the sound of the horn, flute, zither, lyre, harp, pipe, and all kinds\nof music, all the peoples, the nations, and the languages, fell down and worshipped the golden image that Nebuchadnezzar the\nking had set up. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DAN 3:8"}, "Therefore at that time certain Chaldeans came near, and brought accusation against the Jews.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DAN 3:9"}, "They answered Nebuchadnezzar the king, \u201cO king, live for ever!\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DAN 3:10"}, "You, O king, have made a decree, that every man that hears the sound of the horn, flute, zither, lyre, harp, pipe, and\nall kinds of music, shall fall down and worship the golden image;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DAN 3:11"}, "and whoever doesn\u2019t fall down and worship shall be cast into the middle of a burning fiery furnace.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DAN 3:12"}, "There are certain Jews whom you have appointed over the affairs of the province of Babylon: Shadrach, Meshach, and\nAbednego. These men, O king, have not respected you. They don\u2019t serve your gods, and don\u2019t worship the golden image which you\nhave set up.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DAN 3:13"}, "Then Nebuchadnezzar in rage and fury commanded that Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego be brought. Then these men were\nbrought before the king. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DAN 3:14"}, "Nebuchadnezzar answered them, \u201cIs it on purpose, Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego, that you don\u2019t serve my god, nor\nworship the golden image which I have set up? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DAN 3:15"}, "Now if you are ready whenever you hear the sound of the horn, flute, zither, lyre, harp, pipe, and all kinds of music to\nfall down and worship the image which I have made, good; but if you don\u2019t worship, you shall be cast the same hour into the\nmiddle of a burning fiery furnace. Who is that god that will deliver you out of my hands?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DAN 3:16"}, "Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego answered the king, \u201cNebuchadnezzar, we have no need to answer you in this matter.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DAN 3:17"}, "If it happens, our Allah whom we serve is able to deliver us from the burning fiery furnace; and he will deliver us out\nof your hand, O king. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DAN 3:18"}, "But if not, let it be known to you, O king, that we will not serve your gods or worship the golden image which you have\nset up.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DAN 3:19"}, "Then Nebuchadnezzar was full of fury, and the form of his appearance was changed against Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego.\nHe spoke, and commanded that they should heat the furnace seven times more than it was usually heated.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DAN 3:20"}, "He commanded certain mighty men who were in his army to bind Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego, and to cast them into the\nburning fiery furnace. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DAN 3:21"}, "Then these men were bound in their pants, their tunics, and their mantles, and their other clothes, and were cast into\nthe middle of the burning fiery furnace. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DAN 3:22"}, "Therefore because the king\u2019s commandment was urgent, and the furnace exceedingly hot, the flame of the fire killed those\nmen who took up Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DAN 3:23"}, "These three men, Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego, fell down bound into the middle of the burning fiery furnace.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DAN 3:24"}, "Then Nebuchadnezzar the king was astonished, and rose up in haste. He spoke and said to his counsellors, \u201cDidn\u2019t we cast\nthree men bound into the middle of the fire?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They answered the king, \u201cTrue, O king.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DAN 3:25"}, "He answered, \u201cLook, I see four men loose, walking in the middle of the fire, and they are unharmed. The appearance of the\nfourth is like a son of the gods.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DAN 3:26"}, "Then Nebuchadnezzar came near to the mouth of the burning fiery furnace. He spoke and said, \u201cShadrach, Meshach, and\nAbednego, you servants of the Most High Allah, come out, and come here!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Then Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego came out of the middle of the fire.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DAN 3:27"}, "The local governors, the deputies, and the governors, and the king\u2019s counsellors, being gathered together, saw these men,\nthat the fire had no power on their bodies. The hair of their head wasn\u2019t singed. Their pants weren\u2019t changed, the smell of\nfire wasn\u2019t even on them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DAN 3:28"}, "Nebuchadnezzar spoke and said, \u201cBlessed be Allah of Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego, who has sent his angel, and\ndelivered his servants who trusted in him, and have changed the king\u2019s word, and have yielded their bodies, that they might not\nserve nor worship any god, except their own Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "DAN 3:29"}, "Therefore I make a decree, that every people, nation, and language, which speak anything evil against Allah of Shadrach,\nMeshach, and Abednego, shall be cut in pieces, and their houses shall be made a dunghill; because there is no other god who is\nable to deliver like this.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "DAN 3:30"}, "Then the king promoted Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego in the province of Babylon.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "4", "sid": "DAN 4"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DAN 4:1"}, "Nebuchadnezzar the king, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": ["to all the peoples, nations, and languages, who dwell in all the earth:\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": ["Peace be multiplied to you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DAN 4:2"}, "It has seemed good to me to show the signs and wonders that the Most High Allah has worked towards me.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DAN 4:3"}, "How great are his signs! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["How mighty are his wonders! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["His kingdom is an everlasting kingdom. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["His dominion is from generation to generation. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DAN 4:4"}, "I, Nebuchadnezzar, was at rest in my house, and flourishing in my palace.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DAN 4:5"}, "I saw a dream which made me afraid; and the thoughts on my bed and the visions of my head troubled me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DAN 4:6"}, "Therefore made I a decree to bring in all the wise men of Babylon before me, that they might make known to me the\ninterpretation of the dream. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DAN 4:7"}, "Then the magicians, the enchanters, the Chaldeans, and the soothsayers came in; and I told the dream before them; but they\ndidn\u2019t make known to me its interpretation. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DAN 4:8"}, "But at the last Daniel came in before me, whose name was Belteshazzar, according to the name of my god, and in whom is the\nspirit of the holy gods. I told the dream before him, saying, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DAN 4:9"}, "\u201cBelteshazzar, master of the magicians, because I know that the spirit of the holy gods is in you, and no secret troubles\nyou, tell me the visions of my dream that I have seen, and its interpretation.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DAN 4:10"}, "Thus were the visions of my head on my bed: I saw, and behold, a tree in the middle of the earth; and its height was\ngreat. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DAN 4:11"}, "The tree grew, and was strong, and its height reached to the sky, and its sight to the end of all the earth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DAN 4:12"}, "The leaves of it were beautiful, and it had much fruit, and in it was food for all. The animals of the field had shade\nunder it, and the birds of the sky lived in its branches, and all flesh was fed from it.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DAN 4:13"}, "\u201cI saw in the visions of my head on my bed, and behold, a watcher and a holy one came down from the sky.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DAN 4:14"}, "He cried aloud, and said this, \u2018Cut down the tree, and cut off its branches! Shake off its leaves, and scatter its fruit!\nLet the animals get away from under it, and the fowls from its branches.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DAN 4:15"}, "Nevertheless leave the stump of its roots in the earth, even with a band of iron and bronze, in the tender grass of the\nfield; and let it be wet with the dew of the sky. Let his portion be with the animals in the grass of the earth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DAN 4:16"}, "Let his heart be changed from man\u2019s, and let an animal\u2019s heart be given to him. Then let seven times pass over him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DAN 4:17"}, "\u201c\u2018The sentence is by the decree of the watchers, and the demand by the word of the holy ones; to the intent that the\nliving may know that the Most High rules in the kingdom of men, and gives it to whomever he will, and sets up over it the\nlowest of men.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DAN 4:18"}, "\u201cThis dream I, king Nebuchadnezzar, have seen; and you, Belteshazzar, declare the interpretation, because all the wise\nmen of my kingdom are not able to make known to me the interpretation; but you are able; for the spirit of the holy gods is in\nyou.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DAN 4:19"}, "Then Daniel, whose name was Belteshazzar, was stricken mute for a while, and his thoughts troubled him. The king\nanswered, \u201cBelteshazzar, don\u2019t let the dream, or the interpretation, trouble you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": ["Belteshazzar answered, \u201cMy lord, may the dream be for those who hate you, and its interpretation to your adversaries.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DAN 4:20"}, "The tree that you saw, which grew, and was strong, whose height reached to the sky, and its sight to all the earth;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DAN 4:21"}, "whose leaves were beautiful, and its fruit plentiful, and in it was food for all; under which the animals of the field\nlived, and on whose branches the birds of the sky had their habitation:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DAN 4:22"}, "it is you, O king, that have grown and become strong; for your greatness has grown, and reaches to the sky, and your\ndominion to the end of the earth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DAN 4:23"}, "\u201cWhereas the king saw a watcher and a holy one coming down from the sky, and saying, \u2018Cut down the tree, and destroy it;\nnevertheless leave the stump of its roots in the earth, even with a band of iron and bronze, in the tender grass of the field,\nand let it be wet with the dew of the sky. Let his portion be with the animals of the field, until seven times pass over him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DAN 4:24"}, "\u201cThis is the interpretation, O king, and it is the decree of the Most High, which has come on my lord the king:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DAN 4:25"}, "that you shall be driven from men, and your dwelling shall be with the animals of the field. You shall be made to eat\ngrass as oxen, and shall be wet with the dew of the sky, and seven times shall pass over you; until you know that the Most High\nrules in the kingdom of men, and gives it to whomever he will. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DAN 4:26"}, "Whereas they commanded to leave the stump of the roots of the tree; your kingdom shall be sure to you, after that you\nwill have known that the heavens do rule. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DAN 4:27"}, "Therefore, O king, let my counsel be acceptable to you, and break off your sins by righteousness, and your iniquities by\nshowing mercy to the poor. Perhaps there may be a lengthening of your tranquillity.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DAN 4:28"}, "All this came on the king Nebuchadnezzar. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "DAN 4:29"}, "At the end of twelve months he was walking in the royal palace of Babylon.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "DAN 4:30"}, "The king spoke and said, \u201cIs not this great Babylon, which I have built for the royal dwelling place, by the might of my\npower and for the glory of my majesty?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "DAN 4:31"}, "While the word was in the king\u2019s mouth, a voice came from the sky, saying, \u201cO king Nebuchadnezzar, to you it is spoken:\n\u2018The kingdom has departed from you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "DAN 4:32"}, "You shall be driven from men; and your dwelling shall be with the animals of the field. You shall be made to eat grass as\noxen. Seven times shall pass over you, until you know that the Most High rules in the kingdom of men, and gives it to whomever\nhe will.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "DAN 4:33"}, "This was fulfilled the same hour on Nebuchadnezzar. He was driven from men, and ate grass as oxen, and his body was wet\nwith the dew of the sky, until his hair had grown like eagles\u2019 feathers, and his nails like birds\u2019 claws.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "DAN 4:34"}, "At the end of the days I, Nebuchadnezzar, lifted up my eyes to heaven, and my understanding returned to me, and I blessed\nthe Most High, and I praised and honoured him who lives forever;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for his dominion is an everlasting dominion, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his kingdom from generation to generation. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "DAN 4:35"}, "All the inhabitants of the earth are reputed as nothing; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he does according to his will in the army of heaven, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and amongst the inhabitants of the earth; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["and no one can stop his hand, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["or ask him, \u201cWhat are you doing?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "DAN 4:36"}, "At the same time my understanding returned to me; and for the glory of my kingdom, my majesty and brightness returned to\nme. My counsellors and my lords sought me; and I was established in my kingdom, and excellent greatness was added to me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "DAN 4:37"}, "Now I, Nebuchadnezzar, praise and extol and honour the King of heaven; for all his works are truth, and his ways justice;\nand those who walk in pride he is able to abase. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "5", "sid": "DAN 5"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DAN 5:1"}, "Belshazzar the king made a great feast to a thousand of his lords, and drank wine before the thousand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DAN 5:2"}, "Belshazzar, while he tasted the wine, commanded that the golden and silver vessels which Nebuchadnezzar his father had\ntaken out of the temple which was in Jerusalem be brought to him; that the king and his lords, his wives and his concubines,\nmight drink from them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DAN 5:3"}, "Then they brought the golden vessels that were taken out of the temple of Allah\u2019s house which was at Jerusalem; and the\nking and his lords, his wives and his concubines, drank from them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DAN 5:4"}, "They drank wine, and praised the gods of gold, and of silver, of bronze, of iron, of wood, and of stone.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DAN 5:5"}, "In the same hour, the fingers of a man\u2019s hand came out and wrote near the lamp stand on the plaster of the wall of the\nking\u2019s palace. The king saw the part of the hand that wrote. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DAN 5:6"}, "Then the king\u2019s face was changed in him, and his thoughts troubled him; and the joints of his thighs were loosened, and\nhis knees struck one against another. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DAN 5:7"}, "The king cried aloud to bring in the enchanters, the Chaldeans, and the soothsayers. The king spoke and said to the wise\nmen of Babylon, \u201cWhoever reads this writing, and shows me its interpretation, shall be clothed with purple, and have a chain of\ngold about his neck, and shall be the third ruler in the kingdom.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DAN 5:8"}, "Then all the king\u2019s wise men came in; but they could not read the writing, and couldn\u2019t make known to the king the\ninterpretation. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DAN 5:9"}, "Then king Belshazzar was greatly troubled, and his face was changed in him, and his lords were perplexed.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DAN 5:10"}, "The queen by reason of the words of the king and his lords came into the banquet house. The queen spoke and said, \u201cO\nking, live forever; don\u2019t let your thoughts trouble you, nor let your face be changed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DAN 5:11"}, "There is a man in your kingdom, in whom is the spirit of the holy gods; and in the days of your father light and\nunderstanding and wisdom, like the wisdom of the gods, were found in him. The king Nebuchadnezzar your father, yes, the king,\nyour father, made him master of the magicians, enchanters, Chaldeans, and soothsayers;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DAN 5:12"}, "because an excellent spirit, knowledge, understanding, interpreting of dreams, showing of dark sentences, and dissolving\nof doubts were found in the same Daniel, whom the king named Belteshazzar. Now let Daniel be called, and he will show the\ninterpretation.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DAN 5:13"}, "Then Daniel was brought in before the king. The king spoke and said to Daniel, \u201cAre you that Daniel of the children of\nthe captivity of Judah, whom the king my father brought out of Judah?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DAN 5:14"}, "I have heard of you, that the spirit of the gods is in you, and that light, understanding, and excellent wisdom are found\nin you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DAN 5:15"}, "Now the wise men, the enchanters, have been brought in before me, that they should read this writing, and make known to\nme its interpretation; but they could not show the interpretation of the thing.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DAN 5:16"}, "But I have heard of you, that you can give interpretations, and dissolve doubts. Now if you can read the writing, and\nmake known to me its interpretation, you shall be clothed with purple, and have a chain of gold around your neck, and shall be\nthe third ruler in the kingdom.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DAN 5:17"}, "Then Daniel answered before the king, \u201cLet your gifts be to yourself, and give your rewards to another. Nevertheless, I\nwill read the writing to the king, and make known to him the interpretation.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DAN 5:18"}, "\u201cYou, king, the Most High Allah gave Nebuchadnezzar your father the kingdom, and greatness, and glory, and majesty.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DAN 5:19"}, "Because of the greatness that he gave him, all the peoples, nations, and languages trembled and feared before him. He\nkilled whom he wanted to, and he kept alive whom he wanted to. He raised up whom he wanted to, and he put down whom he wanted\nto. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DAN 5:20"}, "But when his heart was lifted up, and his spirit was hardened so that he dealt proudly, he was deposed from his kingly\nthrone, and they took his glory from him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DAN 5:21"}, "He was driven from the sons of men, and his heart was made like the animals\u2019, and his dwelling was with the wild donkeys.\nHe was fed with grass like oxen, and his body was wet with the dew of the sky; until he knew that the Most High Allah rules in\nthe kingdom of men, and that he sets up over it whomever he will.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DAN 5:22"}, "\u201cYou, his son, Belshazzar, have not humbled your heart, though you knew all this,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DAN 5:23"}, "but have lifted up yourself against the Lord of heaven; and they have brought the vessels of his house before you, and\nyou and your lords, your wives, and your concubines, have drunk wine from them. You have praised the gods of silver and gold,\nof bronze, iron, wood, and stone, which don\u2019t see, or hear, or know; and you have not glorified Allah in whose hand your breath\nis, and whose are all your ways. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DAN 5:24"}, "Then the part of the hand was sent from before him, and this writing was inscribed.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DAN 5:25"}, "\u201cThis is the writing that was inscribed: \u2018MENE, MENE, TEKEL, UPHARSIN.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DAN 5:26"}, "\u201cThis is the interpretation of the thing: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "m", "content": ["MENE: Allah has counted your kingdom, and brought it to an end.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "m", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DAN 5:27"}, "TEKEL: you are weighed in the balances, and are found wanting.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "m", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DAN 5:28"}, "PERES: your kingdom is divided, and given to the Medes and Persians.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "DAN 5:29"}, "Then Belshazzar commanded, and they clothed Daniel with purple, and put a chain of gold about his neck, and made\nproclamation concerning him, that he should be the third ruler in the kingdom.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "DAN 5:30"}, "In that night Belshazzar the Chaldean King was slain. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "DAN 5:31"}, "Darius the Mede received the kingdom, being about sixty-two years old.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "6", "sid": "DAN 6"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DAN 6:1"}, "It pleased Darius to set over the kingdom one hundred and twenty local governors, who should be throughout the whole\nkingdom; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DAN 6:2"}, "and over them three presidents, of whom Daniel was one; that these local governors might give account to them, and that\nthe king should suffer no loss. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DAN 6:3"}, "Then this Daniel was distinguished above the presidents and the local governors, because an excellent spirit was in him;\nand the king thought to set him over the whole realm. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DAN 6:4"}, "Then the presidents and the local governors sought to find occasion against Daniel as touching the kingdom; but they could\nfind no occasion or fault, because he was faithful. There wasn\u2019t any error or fault found in him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DAN 6:5"}, "Then these men said, \u201cWe won\u2019t find any occasion against this Daniel, unless we find it against him concerning the law of\nhis Allah.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DAN 6:6"}, "Then these presidents and local governors assembled together to the king, and said this to him, \u201cKing Darius, live\nforever! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DAN 6:7"}, "All the presidents of the kingdom, the deputies and the local governors, the counsellors and the governors, have consulted\ntogether to establish a royal statute, and to make a strong decree, that whoever asks a petition of any god or man for thirty\ndays, except of you, O king, he shall be cast into the den of lions.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DAN 6:8"}, "Now, O king, establish the decree, and sign the writing, that it not be changed, according to the law of the Medes and\nPersians, which doesn\u2019t alter.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DAN 6:9"}, "Therefore king Darius signed the writing and the decree. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DAN 6:10"}, "When Daniel knew that the writing was signed, he went into his house (now his windows were open in his room towards\nJerusalem) and he knelt on his knees three times a day, and prayed, and gave thanks before his Allah, as he did before.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DAN 6:11"}, "Then these men assembled together, and found Daniel making petition and supplication before his Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DAN 6:12"}, "Then they came near, and spoke before the king concerning the king\u2019s decree: \u201cHaven\u2019t you signed a decree that every man\nwho makes a petition to any god or man within thirty days, except to you, O king, shall be cast into the den of lions?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The king answered, \u201cThis thing is true, according to the law of the Medes and Persians, which doesn\u2019t alter.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DAN 6:13"}, "Then they answered and said before the king, \u201cThat Daniel, who is of the children of the captivity of Judah, doesn\u2019t\nrespect you, O king, nor the decree that you have signed, but makes his petition three times a day.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DAN 6:14"}, "Then the king, when he heard these words, was very displeased, and set his heart on Daniel to deliver him; and he\nlaboured until the going down of the sun to rescue him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DAN 6:15"}, "Then these men assembled together to the king, and said to the king, \u201cKnow, O king, that it is a law of the Medes and\nPersians, that no decree nor statute which the king establishes may be changed.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DAN 6:16"}, "Then the king commanded, and they brought Daniel, and cast him into the den of lions. The king spoke and said to Daniel,\n\u201cYour Allah whom you serve continually, he will deliver you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DAN 6:17"}, "A stone was brought, and laid on the mouth of the den; and the king sealed it with his own signet, and with the signet of\nhis lords; that nothing might be changed concerning Daniel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DAN 6:18"}, "Then the king went to his palace, and passed the night fasting. No musical instruments were brought before him; and his\nsleep fled from him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DAN 6:19"}, "Then the king arose very early in the morning, and went in haste to the den of lions.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DAN 6:20"}, "When he came near to the den to Daniel, he cried with a troubled voice. The king spoke and said to Daniel, \u201cDaniel,\nservant of the living Allah, is your Allah, whom you serve continually, able to deliver you from the lions?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DAN 6:21"}, "Then Daniel said to the king, \u201cO king, live forever! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DAN 6:22"}, "My Allah has sent his angel, and has shut the lions\u2019 mouths, and they have not hurt me; because as before him innocence\nwas found in me; and also before you, O king, I have done no harm.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DAN 6:23"}, "Then the king was exceedingly glad, and commanded that they should take Daniel up out of the den. So Daniel was taken up\nout of the den, and no kind of harm was found on him, because he had trusted in his Allah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DAN 6:24"}, "The king commanded, and they brought those men who had accused Daniel, and they cast them into the den of lions, them,\ntheir children, and their wives; and the lions mauled them, and broke all their bones in pieces, before they came to the bottom\nof the den. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DAN 6:25"}, "Then king Darius wrote to all the peoples, nations, and languages, who dwell in all the earth:\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": ["\u201cPeace be multiplied to you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DAN 6:26"}, "\u201cI make a decree that in all the dominion of my kingdom men tremble and fear before Allah of Daniel;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cfor he is the living Allah, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and steadfast forever. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["His kingdom is that which will not be destroyed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["His dominion will be even to the end. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DAN 6:27"}, "He delivers and rescues. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He works signs and wonders in heaven and in earth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who has delivered Daniel from the power of the lions.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DAN 6:28"}, "So this Daniel prospered in the reign of Darius, and in the reign of Dhul-Qarnayn the Persian.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "7", "sid": "DAN 7"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DAN 7:1"}, "In the first year of Belshazzar king of Babylon Daniel had a dream and visions of his head on his bed. Then he wrote the\ndream and told the sum of the matters. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DAN 7:2"}, "Daniel spoke and said, \u201cI saw in my vision by night, and, behold, the four winds of the sky broke out on the great sea.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DAN 7:3"}, "Four great animals came up from the sea, different from one another.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DAN 7:4"}, "\u201cThe first was like a lion, and had eagle\u2019s wings. I watched until its wings were plucked, and it was lifted up from the\nearth, and made to stand on two feet as a man. A man\u2019s heart was given to it.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DAN 7:5"}, "\u201cBehold, there was another animal, a second, like a bear. It was raised up on one side, and three ribs were in its mouth\nbetween its teeth. They said this to it: \u2018Arise! Devour much flesh!\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DAN 7:6"}, "\u201cAfter this I saw, and behold, another, like a leopard, which had on its back four wings of a bird. The animal also had\nfour heads; and dominion was given to it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DAN 7:7"}, "\u201cAfter this I saw in the night visions, and, behold, there was a fourth animal, awesome and powerful, and exceedingly\nstrong. It had great iron teeth. It devoured and broke in pieces, and stamped the residue with its feet. It was different from\nall the animals that were before it. It had ten horns. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DAN 7:8"}, "\u201cI considered the horns, and behold, there came up amongst them another horn, a little one, before which three of the\nfirst horns were plucked up by the roots: and behold, in this horn were eyes like the eyes of a man, and a mouth speaking great\nthings. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DAN 7:9"}, "\u201cI watched until thrones were placed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and one who was ancient of days sat. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["His clothing was white as snow, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the hair of his head like pure wool. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["His throne was fiery flames, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and its wheels burning fire. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DAN 7:10"}, "A fiery stream issued and came out from before him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Thousands of thousands ministered to him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Ten thousand times ten thousand stood before him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["The judgement was set. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The books were opened. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DAN 7:11"}, "\u201cI watched at that time because of the voice of the great words which the horn spoke. I watched even until the animal was\nslain, and its body destroyed, and it was given to be burnt with fire.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DAN 7:12"}, "As for the rest of the animals, their dominion was taken away; yet their lives were prolonged for a season and a time.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DAN 7:13"}, "\u201cI saw in the night visions, and behold, there came with the clouds of the sky one like a son of man, and he came even to\nthe ancient of days, and they brought him near before him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DAN 7:14"}, "Dominion was given him, and glory, and a kingdom, that all the peoples, nations, and languages should serve him. His\ndominion is an everlasting dominion, which will not pass away, and his kingdom that which will not be destroyed.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DAN 7:15"}, "\u201cAs for me, Daniel, my spirit was grieved within my body, and the visions of my head troubled me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DAN 7:16"}, "I came near to one of those who stood by, and asked him the truth concerning all this.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["\u201cSo he told me, and made me know the interpretation of the things.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DAN 7:17"}, "\u2018These great animals, which are four, are four kings, who will arise out of the earth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DAN 7:18"}, "But the saints of the Most High will receive the kingdom, and possess the kingdom forever, even forever and ever.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DAN 7:19"}, "\u201cThen I desired to know the truth concerning the fourth animal, which was different from all of them, exceedingly\nterrible, whose teeth were of iron, and its nails of bronze; which devoured, broke in pieces, and stamped the residue with its\nfeet; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DAN 7:20"}, "and concerning the ten horns that were on its head, and the other horn which came up, and before which three fell, even\nthat horn that had eyes, and a mouth that spoke great things, whose look was more stout than its fellows.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DAN 7:21"}, "I saw, and the same horn made war with the saints, and prevailed against them,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DAN 7:22"}, "until the ancient of days came, and judgement was given to the saints of the Most High, and the time came that the saints\npossessed the kingdom. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DAN 7:23"}, "\u201cThus he said, \u2018The fourth animal will be a fourth kingdom on earth, which will be different from all the kingdoms, and\nwill devour the whole earth, and will tread it down, and break it in pieces.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DAN 7:24"}, "As for the ten horns, ten kings will arise out of this kingdom. Another will arise after them; and he will be different\nfrom the former, and he will put down three kings. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DAN 7:25"}, "He will speak words against the Most High, and will wear out the saints of the Most High. He will plan to change the\ntimes and the law; and they will be given into his hand until a time and times and half a time.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DAN 7:26"}, "\u201c\u2018But the judgement will be set, and they will take away his dominion, to consume and to destroy it to the end.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DAN 7:27"}, "The kingdom and the dominion, and the greatness of the kingdoms under the whole sky, will be given to the people of the\nsaints of the Most High. His kingdom is an everlasting kingdom, and all dominions will serve and obey him.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DAN 7:28"}, "\u201cHere is the end of the matter. As for me, Daniel, my thoughts much troubled me, and my face was changed in me; but I\nkept the matter in my heart.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "8", "sid": "DAN 8"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DAN 8:1"}, "In the third year of the reign of king Belshazzar a vision appeared to me, even to me, Daniel, after that which appeared\nto me at the first. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DAN 8:2"}, "I saw the vision. Now it was so, that when I saw, I was in the citadel of Susa, which is in the province of Elam. I saw in\nthe vision, and I was by the river Ulai. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DAN 8:3"}, "Then I lifted up my eyes, and saw, and behold, there stood before the river a ram which had two horns. The two horns were\nhigh; but one was higher than the other, and the higher came up last.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DAN 8:4"}, "I saw the ram pushing westward, northward, and southward. No animals could stand before him. There wasn\u2019t any who could\ndeliver out of his hand; but he did according to his will, and magnified himself.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DAN 8:5"}, "As I was considering, behold, a male goat came from the west over the surface of the whole earth, and didn\u2019t touch the\nground. The goat had a notable horn between his eyes. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DAN 8:6"}, "He came to the ram that had the two horns, which I saw standing before the river, and ran on him in the fury of his power.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DAN 8:7"}, "I saw him come close to the ram, and he was moved with anger against him, and struck the ram, and broke his two horns.\nThere was no power in the ram to stand before him; but he cast him down to the ground, and trampled on him. There was no one\nwho could deliver the ram out of his hand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DAN 8:8"}, "The male goat magnified himself exceedingly. When he was strong, the great horn was broken; and instead of it there came\nup four notable horns towards the four winds of the sky. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DAN 8:9"}, "Out of one of them came out a little horn, which grew exceedingly great, towards the south, and towards the east, and\ntowards the glorious land. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DAN 8:10"}, "It grew great, even to the army of the sky; and it cast down some of the army and of the stars to the ground, and\ntrampled on them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DAN 8:11"}, "Yes, it magnified itself, even to the prince of the army; and it took away from him the continual burnt offering, and the\nplace of his sanctuary was cast down. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DAN 8:12"}, "The army was given over to it together with the continual burnt offering through disobedience. It cast down truth to the\nground, and it did its pleasure and prospered. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DAN 8:13"}, "Then I heard a holy one speaking; and another holy one said to that certain one who spoke, \u201cHow long will the vision\nabout the continual burnt offering, and the disobedience that makes desolate, to give both the sanctuary and the army to be\ntrodden under foot be?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DAN 8:14"}, "He said to me, \u201cTo two thousand and three hundred evenings and mornings. Then the sanctuary will be cleansed.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DAN 8:15"}, "When I, even I Daniel, had seen the vision, I sought to understand it. Then behold, there stood before me something like\nthe appearance of a man. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DAN 8:16"}, "I heard a man\u2019s voice between the banks of the Ulai, which called, and said, \u201cJabreel, make this man understand the\nvision.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DAN 8:17"}, "So he came near where I stood; and when he came, I was frightened, and fell on my face; but he said to me, \u201cUnderstand,\nson of man; for the vision belongs to the time of the end.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DAN 8:18"}, "Now as he was speaking with me, I fell into a deep sleep with my face towards the ground; but he touched me, and set me\nupright. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DAN 8:19"}, "He said, \u201cBehold, I will make you know what will be in the latter time of the indignation; for it belongs to the\nappointed time of the end. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DAN 8:20"}, "The ram which you saw, that had the two horns, they are the kings of Media and Persia.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DAN 8:21"}, "The rough male goat is the king of Greece. The great horn that is between his eyes is the first king.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DAN 8:22"}, "As for that which was broken, in the place where four stood up, four kingdoms will stand up out of the nation, but not\nwith his power. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DAN 8:23"}, "\u201cIn the latter time of their kingdom, when the transgressors have come to the full, a king of fierce face, and\nunderstanding dark sentences, will stand up. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DAN 8:24"}, "His power will be mighty, but not by his own power. He will destroy awesomely, and will prosper in what he does. He will\ndestroy the mighty ones and the holy people. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DAN 8:25"}, "Through his policy he will cause deceit to prosper in his hand. He will magnify himself in his heart, and he will destroy\nmany in their security. He will also stand up against the prince of princes; but he will be broken without hand.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DAN 8:26"}, "\u201cThe vision of the evenings and mornings which has been told is true; but seal up the vision, for it belongs to many days\nto come.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DAN 8:27"}, "I, Daniel, fainted, and was sick for some days. Then I rose up, and did the king\u2019s business. I wondered at the vision,\nbut no one understood it. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "9", "sid": "DAN 9"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DAN 9:1"}, "In the first year of Darius the son of Ahasuerus, of the offspring of the Medes, who was made king over the realm of the\nChaldeans, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DAN 9:2"}, "in the first year of his reign I, Daniel, understood by the books the number of the years about which the LORD\u2019s\nword", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:2 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["When rendered in ALL CAPITAL LETTERS, \u201cLORD\u201d or \u201cALLAH\u201d is the translation of Allah\u2019s Proper Name.\n"]}], "caller": "+"}, " came to Jeremiah the prophet, for the accomplishing of the desolations of Jerusalem, even seventy years.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DAN 9:3"}, "I set my face to the Lord Allah, to seek by prayer and petitions, with fasting and sackcloth and ashes.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DAN 9:4"}, "I prayed to the LORD my Allah, and made confession, and said,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": ["\u201cOh, Lord, the great and dreadful Allah, who keeps covenant and loving kindness with those who love him and keep his\ncommandments, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DAN 9:5"}, "we have sinned, and have dealt perversely, and have done wickedly, and have rebelled, even turning aside from your\nprecepts and from your ordinances. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DAN 9:6"}, "We haven\u2019t listened to your servants the prophets, who spoke in your name to our kings, our princes, and our fathers, and\nto all the people of the land. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DAN 9:7"}, "\u201cLord, righteousness belongs to you, but to us confusion of face, as it is today; to the men of Judah, and to the\ninhabitants of Jerusalem, and to all Israel, who are near, and who are far off, through all the countries where you have driven\nthem, because of their trespass that they have trespassed against you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DAN 9:8"}, "Lord, to us belongs confusion of face, to our kings, to our princes, and to our fathers, because we have sinned against\nyou. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DAN 9:9"}, "To the Lord our Allah belong mercies and forgiveness; for we have rebelled against him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DAN 9:10"}, "We haven\u2019t obeyed the LORD our Allah\u2019s voice, to walk in his laws, which he set before us by his servants the prophets.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DAN 9:11"}, "Yes, all Israel have transgressed your law, turning aside, that they should not obey your voice.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": ["\u201cTherefore the curse and the oath written in the law of Musa the servant of Allah has been poured out on us; for we have\nsinned against him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DAN 9:12"}, "He has confirmed his words, which he spoke against us, and against our judges who judged us, by bringing on us a great\nevil; for under the whole sky, such has not been done as has been done to Jerusalem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DAN 9:13"}, "As it is written in the law of Musa, all this evil has come on us. Yet we have not entreated the favour of the LORD our\nAllah, that we should turn from our iniquities and have discernment in your truth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DAN 9:14"}, "Therefore the LORD has watched over the evil, and brought it on us; for the LORD our Allah is righteous in all his works\nwhich he does, and we have not obeyed his voice. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DAN 9:15"}, "\u201cNow, Lord our Allah, who has brought your people out of the land of Egypt with a mighty hand, and have gotten yourself\nrenown, as it is today; we have sinned. We have done wickedly. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DAN 9:16"}, "Lord, according to all your righteousness, let your anger and please let your wrath be turned away from your city\nJerusalem, your holy mountain; because for our sins, and for the iniquities of our fathers, Jerusalem and your people have\nbecome a reproach to all who are around us. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DAN 9:17"}, "\u201cNow therefore, our Allah, listen to the prayer of your servant, and to his petitions, and cause your face to shine on\nyour sanctuary that is desolate, for the Lord\u2019s sake. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DAN 9:18"}, "My Allah, turn your ear, and hear. Open your eyes, and see our desolations, and the city which is called by your name;\nfor we do not present our petitions before you for our righteousness, but for your great mercies\u2019 sake.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DAN 9:19"}, "Lord, hear. Lord, forgive. Lord, listen and do. Don\u2019t defer, for your own sake, my Allah, because your city and your\npeople are called by your name.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DAN 9:20"}, "While I was speaking, and praying, and confessing my sin and the sin of my people Israel, and presenting my supplication\nbefore the LORD my Allah for the holy mountain of my Allah; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DAN 9:21"}, "yes, while I was speaking in prayer, the man Jabreel, whom I had seen in the vision at the beginning, being caused to fly\nswiftly, touched me about the time of the evening offering. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DAN 9:22"}, "He instructed me and talked with me, and said, Daniel, \u201cI have now come to give you wisdom and understanding.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DAN 9:23"}, "At the beginning of your petitions the commandment went out, and I have come to tell you; for you are greatly beloved.\nTherefore consider the matter, and understand the vision. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DAN 9:24"}, "\u201cSeventy weeks are decreed on your people and on your holy city, to finish disobedience, and to make an end of sins, and\nto make reconciliation for iniquity, and to bring in everlasting righteousness, and to seal up vision and prophecy, and to\nanoint the most holy. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DAN 9:25"}, "\u201cKnow therefore and discern that from the going out of the commandment to restore and to build Jerusalem to the Anointed\nOne,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:25 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cAnointed One\u201d can also be translated \u201cMessiah\u201d (same as\n\u201cMasih\u201d)."]}], "caller": "+"}, " the prince, will be seven weeks and sixty-two weeks. It will be built again, with street and moat, even in\ntroubled times. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DAN 9:26"}, "After the sixty-two weeks the Anointed One", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:26 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cAnointed One\u201d can also be translated \u201cMessiah\u201d (same as\n\u201cMasih\u201d)."]}], "caller": "+"}, " will be cut off, and will have nothing. The people of the prince who come will destroy the city and the sanctuary.\nIts end will be with a flood, and war will be even to the end. Desolations are determined.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DAN 9:27"}, "He will make a firm covenant with many for one week. In the middle of the week he will cause the sacrifice and the\noffering to cease. On the wing of abominations will come one who makes desolate; and even to the full end, and that determined,\nwrath will be poured out on the desolate.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "10", "sid": "DAN 10"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DAN 10:1"}, "In the third year of Dhul-Qarnayn king of Persia a thing was revealed to Daniel, whose name was called Belteshazzar; and\nthe thing was true, even a great warfare. He understood the thing, and had understanding of the vision.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DAN 10:2"}, "In those days I, Daniel, was mourning three whole weeks. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DAN 10:3"}, "I ate no pleasant bread. No meat or wine came into my mouth. I didn\u2019t anoint myself at all, until three whole weeks were\nfulfilled. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DAN 10:4"}, "In the twenty-fourth day of the first month, as I was by the side of the great river, which is Hiddekel,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DAN 10:5"}, "I lifted up my eyes, and looked, and behold, there was a man clothed in linen, whose thighs were adorned with pure gold of\nUphaz. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DAN 10:6"}, "His body also was like the beryl, and his face as the appearance of lightning, and his eyes as flaming torches. His arms\nand his feet were like burnished bronze. The voice of his words was like the voice of a multitude.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DAN 10:7"}, "I, Daniel, alone saw the vision; for the men who were with me didn\u2019t see the vision; but a great quaking fell on them, and\nthey fled to hide themselves. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DAN 10:8"}, "So I was left alone, and saw this great vision. No strength remained in me; for my face grew deathly pale, and I retained\nno strength. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DAN 10:9"}, "Yet I heard the voice of his words. When I heard the voice of his words, then I fell into a deep sleep on my face, with my\nface towards the ground. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DAN 10:10"}, "Behold, a hand touched me, which set me on my knees and on the palms of my hands.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DAN 10:11"}, "He said to me, \u201cDaniel, you greatly beloved man, understand the words that I speak to you, and stand upright; for I have\nbeen sent to you, now.\u201d When he had spoken this word to me, I stood trembling.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DAN 10:12"}, "Then he said to me, \u201cDon\u2019t be afraid, Daniel; for from the first day that you set your heart to understand, and to humble\nyourself before your Allah, your words were heard. I have come for your words\u2019 sake.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DAN 10:13"}, "But the prince of the kingdom of Persia withstood me twenty-one days; but, behold, Michael, one of the chief princes,\ncame to help me because I remained there with the kings of Persia.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DAN 10:14"}, "Now I have come to make you understand what will happen to your people in the latter days; for the vision is yet for many\ndays.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DAN 10:15"}, "When he had spoken these words to me, I set my face towards the ground, and was mute.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DAN 10:16"}, "Behold, one in the likeness of the sons of men touched my lips. Then I opened my mouth, and spoke and said to him who\nstood before me, \u201cMy lord, by reason of the vision my sorrows have overtaken me, and I retain no strength.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DAN 10:17"}, "For how can the servant of this my lord talk with this my lord? For as for me, immediately there remained no strength in\nme. There was no breath left in me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DAN 10:18"}, "Then one like the appearance of a man touched me again, and he strengthened me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DAN 10:19"}, "He said, \u201cGreatly beloved man, don\u2019t be afraid. Peace be to you. Be strong. Yes, be strong.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["When he spoke to me, I was strengthened, and said, \u201cLet my lord speak; for you have strengthened me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DAN 10:20"}, "Then he said, \u201cDo you know why I have come to you? Now I will return to fight with the prince of Persia. When I go out,\nbehold, the prince of Greece will come. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DAN 10:21"}, "But I will tell you that which is inscribed in the writing of truth. There is no one who holds with me against these, but\nMichael your prince. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "11", "sid": "DAN 11"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DAN 11:1"}, "\u201cAs for me, in the first year of Darius the Mede, I stood up to confirm and strengthen him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DAN 11:2"}, "\u201cNow I will show you the truth. Behold, three more kings will stand up in Persia; and the fourth will be far richer than\nall of them. When he has grown strong through his riches, he will stir up all against the realm of Greece.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DAN 11:3"}, "A mighty king will stand up, who will rule with great dominion, and do according to his will.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DAN 11:4"}, "When he stands up, his kingdom will be broken, and will be divided towards the four winds of the sky, but not to his\nposterity, nor according to his dominion with which he ruled; for his kingdom will be plucked up, even for others besides\nthese. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DAN 11:5"}, "\u201cThe king of the south will be strong. One of his princes will become stronger than him, and have dominion. His dominion\nwill be a great dominion. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DAN 11:6"}, "At the end of years they will join themselves together; and the daughter of the king of the south will come to the king of\nthe north to make an agreement; but she will not retain the strength of her arm. He will also not stand, nor will his arm; but\nshe will be given up, with those who brought her, and he who became the father of her, and he who strengthened her in those\ntimes. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DAN 11:7"}, "\u201cBut out of a shoot from her roots one will stand up in his place, who will come to the army, and will enter into the\nfortress of the king of the north, and will deal against them, and will prevail.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DAN 11:8"}, "He will also carry their gods, with their molten images, and with their goodly vessels of silver and of gold, captive into\nEgypt. He will refrain some years from the king of the north. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DAN 11:9"}, "He will come into the realm of the king of the south, but he will return into his own land.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DAN 11:10"}, "His sons will wage war, and will assemble a multitude of great forces, which will come on, and overflow, and pass\nthrough. They will return and wage war, even to his fortress. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DAN 11:11"}, "\u201cThe king of the south will be moved with anger, and will come out and fight with him, even with the king of the north.\nHe will send out a great multitude, and the multitude will be given into his hand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DAN 11:12"}, "The multitude will be lifted up, and his heart will be exalted. He will cast down tens of thousands, but he won\u2019t\nprevail. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DAN 11:13"}, "The king of the north will return, and will send out a multitude greater than the former. He will come on at the end of\nthe times, even of years, with a great army and with much substance.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DAN 11:14"}, "\u201cIn those times many will stand up against the king of the south. Also the children of the violent amongst your people\nwill lift themselves up to establish the vision; but they will fall.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DAN 11:15"}, "So the king of the north will come and cast up a mound, and take a well-fortified city. The forces of the south won\u2019t\nstand, neither will his chosen people, neither will there be any strength to stand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DAN 11:16"}, "But he who comes against him will do according to his own will, and no one will stand before him. He will stand in the\nglorious land, and destruction will be in his hand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DAN 11:17"}, "He will set his face to come with the strength of his whole kingdom, and with him equitable conditions. He will perform\nthem. He will give him the daughter of women, to corrupt her; but she will not stand, and won\u2019t be for him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DAN 11:18"}, "After this he will turn his face to the islands, and will take many; but a prince will cause the reproach offered by him\nto cease. Yes, moreover, he will cause his reproach to turn on him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DAN 11:19"}, "Then he will turn his face towards the fortresses of his own land; but he will stumble and fall, and won\u2019t be found.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DAN 11:20"}, "\u201cThen one who will cause a tax collector to pass through the kingdom to maintain its glory will stand up in his place;\nbut within few days he shall be destroyed, not in anger, and not in battle.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DAN 11:21"}, "\u201cIn his place a contemptible person will stand up, to whom they had not given the honour of the kingdom; but he will come\nin time of security, and will obtain the kingdom by flatteries. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DAN 11:22"}, "The overwhelming forces will be overwhelmed from before him, and will be broken. Yes, also the prince of the covenant.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DAN 11:23"}, "After the treaty made with him he will work deceitfully; for he will come up, and will become strong, with a small\npeople. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DAN 11:24"}, "In time of security he will come even on the fattest places of the province. He will do that which his fathers have not\ndone, nor his fathers\u2019 fathers. He will scatter amongst them prey, plunder, and substance. Yes, he will devise his plans\nagainst the strongholds, even for a time. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DAN 11:25"}, "\u201cHe will stir up his power and his courage against the king of the south with a great army; and the king of the south\nwill wage war in battle with an exceedingly great and mighty army; but he won\u2019t stand; for they will devise plans against him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DAN 11:26"}, "Yes, those who eat of his dainties will destroy him, and his army will be swept away. Many will fall down slain.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DAN 11:27"}, "As for both these kings, their hearts will be to do mischief, and they will speak lies at one table; but it won\u2019t\nprosper, for the end will still be at the appointed time. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DAN 11:28"}, "Then he will return into his land with great wealth. His heart will be against the holy covenant. He will take action,\nand return to his own land. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "DAN 11:29"}, "\u201cHe will return at the appointed time, and come into the south; but it won\u2019t be in the latter time as it was in the\nformer. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "DAN 11:30"}, "For ships of Kittim will come against him. Therefore he will be grieved, and will return, and have indignation against\nthe holy covenant, and will take action. He will even return, and have regard to those who forsake the holy covenant.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "DAN 11:31"}, "\u201cForces will stand on his part, and they will profane the sanctuary, even the fortress, and will take away the continual\nburnt offering. Then they will set up the abomination that makes desolate.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "DAN 11:32"}, "He will corrupt those who do wickedly against the covenant by flatteries; but the people who know their Allah will be\nstrong, and take action. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "DAN 11:33"}, "\u201cThose who are wise amongst the people will instruct many; yet they will fall by the sword and by flame, by captivity and\nby plunder, many days. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "DAN 11:34"}, "Now when they fall, they will be helped with a little help; but many will join themselves to them with flatteries.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "DAN 11:35"}, "Some of those who are wise will fall, to refine them, and to purify, and to make them white, even to the time of the end;\nbecause it is yet for the time appointed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "DAN 11:36"}, "\u201cThe king will do according to his will. He will exalt himself, and magnify himself above every god, and will speak\nmarvellous things against Allah of gods. He will prosper until the indignation is accomplished; for that which is determined\nwill be done. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "DAN 11:37"}, "He won\u2019t regard the gods of his fathers, or the desire of women, or regard any god; for he will magnify himself above\nall. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "DAN 11:38"}, "But in his place he will honour the god of fortresses. He will honour a god whom his fathers didn\u2019t know with gold,\nsilver, and with precious stones and pleasant things. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "DAN 11:39"}, "He will deal with the strongest fortresses by the help of a foreign god. He will increase with glory whoever acknowledges\nhim. He will cause them to rule over many, and will divide the land for a price.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "DAN 11:40"}, "\u201cAt the time of the end the king of the south will contend with him; and the king of the north will come against him like\na whirlwind, with chariots, with horsemen, and with many ships. He will enter into the countries, and will overflow and pass\nthrough. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "DAN 11:41"}, "He will enter also into the glorious land, and many countries will be overthrown; but these will be delivered out of his\nhand: Edom, Moab, and the chief of the children of Ammon. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "DAN 11:42"}, "He will also stretch out his hand on the countries. The land of Egypt won\u2019t escape.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "DAN 11:43"}, "But he will have power over the treasures of gold and of silver, and over all the precious things of Egypt. The Libyans\nand the Ethiopians will be at his steps. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "DAN 11:44"}, "But news out of the east and out of the north will trouble him; and he will go out with great fury to destroy and utterly\nto sweep away many. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "DAN 11:45"}, "He will plant the tents of his palace between the sea and the glorious holy mountain; yet he will come to his end, and no\none will help him. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "12", "sid": "DAN 12"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DAN 12:1"}, "\u201cAt that time Michael will stand up, the great prince who stands for the children of your people; and there will be a time\nof trouble, such as never was since there was a nation even to that same time. At that time your people will be delivered,\neveryone who is found written in the book. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DAN 12:2"}, "Many of those who sleep in the dust of the earth will awake, some to everlasting life, and some to shame and everlasting\ncontempt. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DAN 12:3"}, "Those who are wise will shine as the brightness of the expanse. Those who turn many to righteousness will shine as the\nstars forever and ever. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DAN 12:4"}, "But you, Daniel, shut up the words, and seal the book, even to the time of the end. Many will run back and forth, and\nknowledge will be increased.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DAN 12:5"}, "Then I, Daniel, looked, and behold, two others stood, one on the river bank on this side, and the other on the river bank\non that side. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DAN 12:6"}, "One said to the man clothed in linen, who was above the waters of the river, \u201cHow long will it be to the end of these\nwonders?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DAN 12:7"}, "I heard the man clothed in linen, who was above the waters of the river, when he held up his right hand and his left hand\nto heaven, and swore by him who lives forever that it will be for a time, times, and a half; and when they have finished\nbreaking in pieces the power of the holy people, all these things will be finished.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DAN 12:8"}, "I heard, but I didn\u2019t understand. Then I said, \u201cMy lord, what will be the outcome of these things?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DAN 12:9"}, "He said, \u201cGo your way, Daniel; for the words are shut up and sealed until the time of the end.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DAN 12:10"}, "Many will purify themselves, and make themselves white, and be refined; but the wicked will do wickedly; and none of the\nwicked will understand; but those who are wise will understand. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DAN 12:11"}, "\u201cFrom the time that the continual burnt offering is taken away, and the abomination that makes desolate set up, there\nwill be one thousand and two hundred and ninety days. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DAN 12:12"}, "Blessed is he who waits, and comes to the one thousand and three hundred and thirty-five days.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DAN 12:13"}, "\u201cBut go your way until the end; for you will rest, and will stand in your inheritance at the end of the days.\u201d\n"]}]}